-- Update existing Cybersecurity lessons with rich content
UPDATE public.lessons SET
  content = E'# What is Cybersecurity?\n\n## Introduction\n\nCybersecurity is the practice of protecting systems, networks, and programs from digital attacks. These cyberattacks are usually aimed at accessing, changing, or destroying sensitive information, extorting money from users, or interrupting normal business processes.\n\n## Why Cybersecurity Matters\n\n- **Data Protection**: Safeguarding personal and business information\n- **Financial Security**: Preventing monetary losses from breaches\n- **Business Continuity**: Ensuring operations continue without disruption\n- **Reputation Management**: Maintaining trust with customers and partners\n\n## Key Concepts\n\n1. **Confidentiality**: Ensuring information is accessible only to authorized users\n2. **Integrity**: Maintaining accuracy and completeness of data\n3. **Availability**: Ensuring authorized users have access when needed\n\n## Career Opportunities\n\nThe cybersecurity field offers numerous career paths:\n- Security Analyst\n- Penetration Tester\n- Security Architect\n- Chief Information Security Officer (CISO)\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\nBy the end of this lesson, you will:\n- Understand the fundamentals of cybersecurity\n- Recognize the importance of security in modern organizations\n- Identify basic security principles\n- Explore career opportunities in the field',
  video_url = 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/inWWhr5tnEA',
  duration_minutes = 30
WHERE title = 'What is Cybersecurity?';

UPDATE public.lessons SET
  content = E'# Common Cyber Threats\n\n## Overview\n\nUnderstanding common cyber threats is essential for protecting yourself and your organization. This lesson covers the most prevalent types of cyberattacks.\n\n## Types of Threats\n\n### 1. Malware\n- **Viruses**: Self-replicating programs that attach to files\n- **Worms**: Standalone malware that spreads across networks\n- **Trojans**: Malicious code disguised as legitimate software\n- **Ransomware**: Encrypts data and demands payment for decryption\n\n### 2. Phishing\n- Email-based attacks that trick users into revealing sensitive information\n- Spear phishing targets specific individuals\n- Whaling targets high-profile executives\n\n### 3. Social Engineering\n- Manipulating people into divulging confidential information\n- Pretexting: Creating false scenarios\n- Baiting: Offering something enticing\n- Tailgating: Following authorized personnel\n\n### 4. DDoS Attacks\n- Overwhelming systems with traffic\n- Disrupting normal operations\n- Often used for extortion\n\n## Real-World Examples\n\n- **WannaCry Ransomware (2017)**: Affected 200,000+ computers worldwide\n- **Equifax Breach (2017)**: Exposed data of 147 million people\n- **SolarWinds Attack (2020)**: Compromised government and corporate networks\n\n## Protection Strategies\n\n1. Keep software updated\n2. Use strong, unique passwords\n3. Enable multi-factor authentication\n4. Be cautious with email attachments\n5. Regular backups\n6. Security awareness training\n\n## Key Takeaways\n\n- Cyber threats are constantly evolving\n- Human error is often the weakest link\n- Prevention is more effective than remediation\n- Staying informed is crucial',
  video_url = 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/hxHqE2W8scQs',
  duration_minutes = 45
WHERE title = 'Common Cyber Threats';

UPDATE public.lessons SET
  content = E'# Career Paths in Cybersecurity\n\n## Industry Overview\n\nThe cybersecurity industry is experiencing unprecedented growth, with millions of unfilled positions worldwide. This lesson explores various career paths and what it takes to succeed.\n\n## Entry-Level Positions\n\n### Security Analyst\n- **Salary Range**: $50,000 - $75,000\n- **Responsibilities**: Monitor networks, investigate incidents, implement security measures\n- **Required Skills**: Network fundamentals, security tools, analytical thinking\n\n### IT Support Specialist (Security Focus)\n- **Salary Range**: $40,000 - $60,000\n- **Responsibilities**: User support, basic security tasks, documentation\n- **Required Skills**: Customer service, troubleshooting, basic security knowledge\n\n## Mid-Level Positions\n\n### Penetration Tester\n- **Salary Range**: $75,000 - $120,000\n- **Responsibilities**: Ethical hacking, vulnerability assessment, security testing\n- **Required Skills**: Programming, networking, security tools, creativity\n\n### Security Engineer\n- **Salary Range**: $80,000 - $130,000\n- **Responsibilities**: Design security systems, implement solutions, maintain infrastructure\n- **Required Skills**: System architecture, security protocols, automation\n\n### Incident Response Specialist\n- **Salary Range**: $70,000 - $110,000\n- **Responsibilities**: Respond to breaches, forensic analysis, recovery planning\n- **Required Skills**: Quick thinking, forensics, communication\n\n## Senior-Level Positions\n\n### Security Architect\n- **Salary Range**: $120,000 - $180,000\n- **Responsibilities**: Design enterprise security, strategic planning, team leadership\n- **Required Skills**: Advanced architecture, business acumen, leadership\n\n### Chief Information Security Officer (CISO)\n- **Salary Range**: $150,000 - $400,000+\n- **Responsibilities**: Overall security strategy, risk management, board reporting\n- **Required Skills**: Executive leadership, business strategy, communication\n\n## Certifications\n\n### Entry-Level\n- CompTIA Security+\n- Certified Ethical Hacker (CEH)\n- GIAC Security Essentials (GSEC)\n\n### Advanced\n- Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP)\n- Offensive Security Certified Professional (OSCP)\n- Certified Information Security Manager (CISM)\n\n## Skills Development Path\n\n1. **Foundation** (0-2 years)\n   - Networking basics\n   - Operating systems\n   - Security fundamentals\n\n2. **Specialization** (2-5 years)\n   - Choose focus area\n   - Gain certifications\n   - Hands-on experience\n\n3. **Leadership** (5+ years)\n   - Team management\n   - Strategic thinking\n   - Business alignment\n\n## Industry Sectors\n\n- **Finance**: Banks, insurance, fintech\n- **Healthcare**: Hospitals, pharma, health tech\n- **Government**: Federal, state, local agencies\n- **Technology**: Software companies, cloud providers\n- **Consulting**: Security firms, advisory services\n\n## Job Market Outlook\n\n- **Growth Rate**: 31% (2019-2029) - Much faster than average\n- **Job Openings**: 3.5 million unfilled positions globally\n- **Demand**: Increasing due to digital transformation\n- **Remote Work**: Many positions offer flexibility\n\n## Getting Started\n\n1. Complete foundational training\n2. Earn entry-level certification\n3. Build home lab for practice\n4. Contribute to open-source projects\n5. Network with professionals\n6. Apply for internships or entry-level roles\n\n## Resources\n\n- **Online Platforms**: TryHackMe, HackTheBox, Cybrary\n- **Communities**: Reddit r/cybersecurity, Discord servers\n- **Conferences**: DEF CON, Black Hat, RSA Conference\n- **Books**: "The Web Application Hacker''s Handbook", "Metasploit"\n\n## Success Tips\n\n- Stay curious and keep learning\n- Practice hands-on skills regularly\n- Build a professional network\n- Document your projects\n- Contribute to the community\n- Stay updated on latest threats',
  video_url = 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/M_i4FqzJLU8',
  duration_minutes = 30
WHERE title = 'Career Paths in Cybersecurity';

